cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper is primarily focused on network security and anomaly detection in network traffic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses various machine learning and signal analysis techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with network infrastructure, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper presents a framework for network anomaly detection, which could also place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
